<h1><span style="font-size: 24pt;">Indianapolis Metropolitan High School</span></h1>
<p> </p>
<p>Indianapolis Metropolitan High School is a free public school offering a high school education to students in grades 9-12. Indianapolis Met is a best-fit school for students experiencing circumstances that may present a barrier to education. Our school places an emphasis on ensuring students enroll in college or enter into a career that offers a living wage post-graduation.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Indianapolis Met is designed to serve students who are experiencing circumstances that may become barriers to their education. Barriers may include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Teen pregnancy</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Teen parenting</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Involvement in foster care</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Homelessness</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Identified for special education</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-size: 16px;">Involvement with criminal justice</span></li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
